<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Board1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Board,</orth> subst. (cf. <emph>aboard</emph>). 1) a piece of timber sawed thin: <cit><quote>ships are but --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 22</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) table: <cit><quote>fed from my trencher, kneeled down at the b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I would have left it on the b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 6, 51</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>at b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 18</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.64.18" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 64</bibl>. <cit><quote>b. and bed:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 31</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.148" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 24</bibl>.
<lb />3) an authorized assembly: <cit><quote>the honourable b. of council,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 79</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>